Subversion from stock AWS AMI  used on OnDemand Elastic Bamboo has been upgraded  (from 1.6.17 to 1.7.9) without any notice and without any note on [OnDemand Application Versions page.|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AOD/Atlassian+OnDemand+Application+Versions]

*_Pre-update_*
{noformat}
[root@ip-~]# rpm -qa | grep -i subversion
subversion-1.6.17-1.14.amzn1.i686
{noformat} 

*_Post-update_*
{noformat}
[root@ip-~]# rpm -qa | grep -i subversion
subversion-libs-1.7.9-1.28.amzn1.i686
subversion-1.7.9-1.28.amzn1.i686
{noformat}

Please update the documentation, warning customers about Elastic Images update.

First step is unclear because it shows the following error:

{quote}
The page _adminLoginGeneral could not be found.
{quote}

the error is repeated on the next part on the same page. As a result, I have no idea what the first step should be about.

The location: https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AOD/Enabling+DVCS+smart+commits

U can view the issue here:
https://naturalint.atlassian.net/browse/AD-9


{panel:title=Reply from Support|titleBGColor=limegreen}
It's not possible to change the default way the values of a Multi Checkbox field are displayed in the Issue View in Jira. A custom add-on, though (if you're not on OnDemand), might be used to modify it.
{panel}
